	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Wednesday&#44; 18th Aug</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear. <addressee>Mr. Leeser.</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yesterday I forwarded an article for<lb/> your approval &#38;c and I remember now that in the<lb/> Hurry of copying the last part I omitted to give the <hi rend="underline">notes</hi><lb/> I enclose them. You can give what I send to the<lb/> printer instead of the original page.  The note about<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Laws of Divorce</hi> I think will apply to <hi rend="underline"><persName>Sim Abraham</persName></hi><lb/> last week&#44; <persName>Mrs. Motta</persName> gave me some Spanish books<lb/> belonging to old <persName>Mr Aziredo<add>&#63;</add></persName>&#44; among them is the<lb/> &#8220;Hoboth Hallebaboth&#8221; also in Spanish and in looking<lb/> over it I found this passage. I referred to <persName>Dr. E.</persName> who<lb/> has a copy in Hebrew and between us you have a<lb/> &#8220;note&#8221; which strengthens the position you took in the<lb/> <placeName>Cleveland</placeName> affair without saving you the <hi rend="underline">trouble</hi> to answer him. If you have not a copy in Hebrew<lb/> and <del>want</del> can use this one in Spanish. I will <hi rend="underline">give it</hi> to<lb/> you. I also can supply you with a sett of <date><sic>Rorsanna</sic></date><add>&#63;</add><lb/> &#38; <date>kippur</date> and daily prayers &#40;A Hazans copy with prayers for the whole<lb/> year&#41; also in Spanish. As I have three or four setts.<lb/> Shall I send them if I can find a <sic>covenent</sic> oppty&#63;<lb/> I have also two copies of the Pentateuch in Spanish with copious notes in Hebrew<lb/> from <hi rend="underline">all the learned sciences</hi><add>&#63;</add>.  Will you have <hi rend="underline">one</hi>&#63; <hi rend="underline">one</hi> copy is enough<lb/> for me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have not seen the sheet of your bible sent to <persName>M Serin<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> he is a little hurt I think that you have not written to him If<lb/> you can spare time. you might write him a few lines<lb/> my wife is not very well. She sends her kind regards. <persName>Mrs<lb/> Motta</persName> tells me she has some money to send you and promised it</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>last week when I see her I will get it and remit what I have also<lb/> I had no time to <add>&#63;</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours sincerely</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">J. N. Carvalho</persName></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><hi rend="underline">Paid</hi></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Editor of Occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Walnut St near Thirteenth</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
